I just had to write this comment because I am in love with Akudo. The customer support is fantastic, the app is so user-friendly and it has helped me take care of my child's expenses in a much smoother way. It is also hassle-free because my child can either pay at a shop or enter the bill using the app - they are too young to use a debit card. I will never go back to cash.

I am a mother of two and I am really impressed by how Akudo has changed the way we manage money for our kids. It just takes two minutes to onboard every member of the family and you can even set up Auto-tas in case your children need some help. The process is easy and convenient.

I was really struggling to teach my son about money. I was going through a lot of trouble with him asking for money, not understanding how much things cost, and even making impulse purchases. After Akudo came into our lives, he understands his own limits and can buy what he needs without overspending.

I'm a single mom, and I work all the time. Akudo has been so helpful! I can't tell you how many times my son has forgotten his debit card or ID when we go out to eat. With Akudo, it's so easy for me to add money to his account, even if I'm on the other side of town. He loves the card too btw.
I was constantly going to the ATM to do my daughter's banking and now she can do it with her own card. It also saves me a lot of time in the process, as well.

I have been using Akudo for about a year now and it has made our lives so much easier. We have been trying to teach our 11 year old some money management skills, but with the help of Akudo we have been able to do it in a much easier way. We can track their expenses, block cards when necessary and set up customised tas.

As a parent, I really appreciate this product. It takes away the need for me to control my teenager's account after they have become independent and the hassles of managing the account. Now I can spend time with my family instead of worrying about a kid who thinks they have it all figured out.
